

Overview: 
A one-shot GCS batch ingestion job — fetch all PGP users → save profile JSON + raw txt to pgp/23andme/profiles/ and pgp/23andme/raw_txt/ in the bucket, with per-user error files if any fetch fails. 

index.js:
    Node.js job — fetches all PGP 23andMe profiles + raw txt files from my.pgp-hms.org and uploads them to a Google Cloud Storage bucket
package.json:
	ESM module, single dep: @google-cloud/storage
dockerfile:
    Container image for the job
cloudInstructions:
    Manual steps to build & deploy as a Cloud Run Job on GCP


✅ Step 1: Create a project folder

On your machine:

mkdir pgp-23andme-job
cd pgp-23andme-job

✅ Step 2: Add your files

Inside that folder:

pgp-23andme-job/
  ├── index.js
  ├── package.json
  └── Dockerfile   (if using Option 2)

✅ Step 3: Paste contents
📄 package.json
{
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": { "start": "node index.js" },
  "dependencies": {
    "@google-cloud/storage": "^7.16.0"
  }
}
//---------------------------------------
📄 index.js

Your job logic (fetch PGP + upload to GCS)

📄 Dockerfile (if using container build)
FROM node:20
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install
COPY . .
CMD ["node", "index.js"]
✅ Step 4: Deploy from THIS folder

👉 This is critical

Run commands inside pgp-23andme-job/

gcloud builds submit --tag gcr.io/YOUR_PROJECT_ID/pgp-job

then:

gcloud run jobs deploy pgp-23andme-import \
  --image gcr.io/YOUR_PROJECT_ID/pgp-job \
  --region us-central1 \
  --set-env-vars BUCKET_NAME=YOUR_BUCKET_NAME,WORKER_BASE=YOUR_WORKER

  ----------------------------
